I love this! I just got back from Italy and am totally psyched to do some Italian-inspired baking. This rosemary-semolina loaf was just right. I rolled it into two rounds instead of one, so I'd have one to give away and one to keep. I also forgot to score the final proofed loaf before baking, but it came out just fine. Delicious crunchy crust with soft pillowy but dense crumb inside.

