Rating: 4
I made this bread the way the recipe was written the first time. The second time I decided to put all the ingredients in my bread machine on the dough only cycle (in the order the manufacurer suggests) and let 'er rip. Then I formed the round loaf, let it rise the second time and baked it. It was just as delicious as it was the first time and a whole lot easier!

Rating: 3
Really good dinner bread. I served this with marinated, grilled chicken and a cool cous cous salad. I changed the procedure a little. After the sponge sits for the 45 minutes, I put it on my kitchenaid attached with a dough hook and then slowly added the rest of the ingredients--no need to do two separate mixing bowls. I did almost all the kneading with the machine and just finished kneading by hand for the last minute or so. I found that I only needed about 45 minutes on the second rise and 30 minutes on the third rise. Easy and delicious.

Rating: 3
This bread was surprisingly easy, has a good crumb and a wonderful flavor. I didn't make it in a round but made 2 free form loaves and froze one. Terrific with soup. Definitely a keeper!

